  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, if your card has been inserted into an ATM, there are a few ways to confirm this:\n\n1. **ATM Screen**: Once the card is inserted, the ATM screen will typically display a prompt asking for your PIN or to select a transaction type. If the screen remains blank or doesn\u2019t respond, the card may not have been inserted correctly.\n\n2. **ATM Sounds**: Most ATMs make a sound when a card is inserted or ejected. If you hear a beep or click, it indicates the card has been accepted.\n\n3. **Card Slot Check**: If the card is fully inserted, it should no longer be visible outside the ATM slot. If you see part of the card protruding, it may not have been inserted properly.\n\n4. **ATM Message**: If the card is damaged, expired, or not inserted correctly, the ATM may display an error message or prompt you to reinsert the card.\n\n5. **Physical Feedback**: Some ATMs may have a slight vibration or feedback when the card is successfully inserted.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure whether your card has been inserted, avoid leaving the ATM unattended. If the card is not accepted or you suspect it\u2019s stuck, contact your bank or the ATM operator immediately. Always cover the keypad when entering your PIN to protect your information.",
